    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20200920/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-09-20"><time>2020-09-20</time></a>
        - <span>INSIGHT</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>THE CEO</p>
    <p>Tony Lom­bardo has been Lendlease’s chief ex­ec­u­tive for Asia since May 2016. He is 46 years old.</p>
    <p>He was pre­vi­ously group chief fi­nan­cial of­fi­cer of Lendlease and head of strat­egy and merg­ers/ac­qui­si­tions. He came to Lendlease af­ter nearly a decade with GE and GE Cap­i­tal.</p>
    <p>Schooled at Cathe­dral Col­lege and St Joseph’s Col­lege in Mel­bourne, Mr Lom­bardo is a char­tered ac­coun­tant and has a Bach­e­lor of Busi­ness in ac­count­ing and fi­nance from RMIT Univer­sity.</p>
    <p>He was born into a fam­ily of five chil­dren, and his grand­par­ents were mi­grants from Italy who had set­tled in Aus­tralia.</p>
    <p>Mr Lom­bardo is mar­ried to May Chen, a Malaysia-born Aus­tralian.</p>
    <p>THE COM­PANY</p>
    <p>Lendlease is a con­struc­tion, in­fra­struc­ture and real es­tate com­pany based in Syd­ney, Aus­tralia.</p>
    <p>Founded in 1958, it op­er­ates in four re­gions – Aus­tralia, Asia, Europe and the Amer­i­cas. Lendlease has 1,400 em­ploy­ees in Asia among ap­prox­i­mately 10,900 world­wide.</p>
    <p>The group cur­rently has A$1.5 bil­lion (S$1.49 bil­lion) in­vested in Asia, up from A$600 mil­lion five years ago. It has had a pres­ence in Sin­ga­pore – its Asia head­quar­ters – since 1973. Lendlease Global Com­mer­cial Reit is listed in Sin­ga­pore.</p>
    <p>Group rev­enue was A$13 bil­lion in this fi­nan­cial year, cov­er­ing the pe­riod from July 2019 to June 2020. Lendlease has a de­vel­op­ment pipe­line of A$113 bil­lion, ac­cord­ing to its lat­est an­nual re­port. It also has funds un­der man­age­ment of A$36 bil­lion and as­sets un­der man­age­ment of A$29 bil­lion.</p>
    <p>Last year, Lendlease was No. 5, be­hind four fi­nan­cial services com­pa­nies, in LinkedIn’s list of top 25 com­pa­nies where Aus­tralians want to work.</p>


